Dear Belizean cyclist, 

There's an election tomorrow. It is an opportunity to bring in a new era of cycling—one of hope, prosperity, and pride. 

Over the last three years, my family and I have gone out of our way to show Belizean cycling to the world and invite athletes to participate in events in the US, like Tulsa Tough in Tulsa, Oklahoma, and Intelligencia Cup in Chicago. We did this without having to be asked, and we did this out of our own pockets. We want to be more involved by helping lead the cycling federation down a path to success.

I will personally help with getting better sponsors for the national team, creating a calendar that makes growth in our athletes, creating more exciting events for cycling in Belize, and building the inforstrutct needed to take Belize cycling to the next level. We will also make space for promising athletes on our pro teams; like we did with Oscar Quiros on the Miami blazers. 

I will not be able to make it to Belize until January. But I'm supporting Alicia Thompson for President and encouraging you to go vote. Your voice matters, and you hold your destiny is in your hands. I will do my part, if you do yours.

Photo #1: Discussing patience, strategic fighting, and navigating the front of a group in the last five laps with JP.

Photo #2: Wishing Greg luck and encouraging him to understand that progress takes time, racing is highly competitive, and conserving energy to capitalize on opportunities.

CRIT CONQUERED🔥 It was an epic day celebrating the inaugural #CRITchampionship Tour with you in @stpetefl! Thank you to all the teams who showed face, the crowd who energized the athletes and our incredible sponsors who supported this movement!

 #critracing #stpetersburgflorida #criterium #crit #bikes #bikeracing #bikeracer #cycling #racing #procycling @crockervideo

Here’s everything you need to know about @critchampionship and how it’s going to change cycling in the US. 

The weekend kicked off with all of the teams arriving and staying at the same hotel. The energy and vibes were on point, creating togetherness and camaraderie that led to safe and more respectable racing.

We had some pretty incredible partners help us expand the demographics that interacted with the race, including yoga with @vuoriclothing and a community group ride with @pedalmafia, who collaborated with amazing local artists @dustinharewood 

We put on the junior race where we had kids of all ages ripping around our course, having fun before they got to see the pros go out on it. You have to start them early they say.

We worked out a system to get riders' names and numbers on their jerseys as we start to develop ways to give athletes an identity and tell their stories.

We lined teams up on a grid, which has been done before. It visualizes how much of a team sport crits are.

We also showcased our new racing format, breaking the race into four quarters. It was exciting watching teams test their tactics, not only to try to gain points to win the team classification but also to win the race. I’m proud of my boy and future world tour rider @lukelamperti for making it look easy. Him and the @l39ion.la boys (@nationsnumber1beast @twcycling @ederfrayre @boardmanito) brought their usual intensity and Sam didn’t even have to be there. Very proud of the teams who made this event so special.

A massive shout-out to all of the partners who believed in the vision and didn’t shy away when things got hard. It’s easy to do the right thing when everyone’s looking… 📷 @kitkarzen

🔥 Hype it up for @l39ion.la leading in victory at the #CRITchampionship Tour last weekend in @stpetefl! THANK you to all the teams who came together to make it an epic weekend of riding, energized camaraderie, and sharing this experience with the community ➡️ We couldn’t do it without you!
